1. Correct Application and Responsibility The Concept Principle is
intended to function as described when applied in good faith and in accordance
with the inherent definition, including the stated formulation and purpose.
““The inalienable right to pursue happiness is not about your happiness. It’s
about others happiness. You do whatever you want but you do it without anything
you’re doing infringing upon or forgoing choice within anyone else’s pursuit of
happiness, or anything you’re thinking or saying forcing anyone to listen or
adhere. This applies universally. Everyone does whatever they like within the
bounds that no one intentionally fucks anyone over, no one must adhere to others
ideas or lifestyles without consent, the individual places others ahead of the
self in order to facilitate for the inalienable right for themselves and the
rest of humanity. Others put the individual and humanity ahead of themselves.
Unintended infringement is resolved mutually naturally. No one wants to fuck
anyone over. This solves all problems humanity causes for itself. Anything else
is against us. “ -Branton Allan Baker (like a charming folk hero)”
